            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Today, I challenge DSG to make reform a topic for campus discourse, to open up discussions to student organizations and residential communities that this decision will effect and to take the time to create a more effective system through a democratic process.  It may become messy, but redefining the way we do student government will be integral to its future and the future of the Duke student experience.</p>
<p>Let’s engage each other and create a system that works for all students because it involves all students.</p>
<p><i>Jay Sullivan is a Trinity junior. His column runs every other semester. </i><br></p>

